cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with deep learning models for visual domain adaptation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new CNN architecture that optimizes for domain invariance and uses a soft label distribution matching loss to transfer information between tasks. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using natural language processing techniques for text-based domain adaptation, which could place it in the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on standard benchmark visual domain adaptation tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
